    {
      "id": "type-definition-contract-required-fields",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Required Fields",
      "position": {
        "x": -220,
        "y": 160
      },
      "width": 680,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Required Fields\n\nA valid type definition should declare:\n- `name`: the visible legend-facing type name\n- `key`: a stable internal identifier\n- `classRef`: the node class authority that implements the type\n- `meaning`: the semantic meaning consumers should rely on\n\nSupporting fields like `description`, `category`, and `status` help library organization but do not replace the required core."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "type-definition-contract-boundaries",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Boundaries",
      "position": {
        "x": 1040,
        "y": -40
      },
      "width": 520,
      "height": 280,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Boundaries\n\n`type` is declared data, not a view-owned property.\n\nA `ui-view` may display the type, but the type definition node owns the semantic identity. This keeps legend population, consumer behavior, and rendering authority aligned."
      }
    }
